category.name: food/drink
description: Do you love trying new vegetarian & vegan restaurants? Do you enjoy the company of fellow vegetarians & vegans? Do you wish to dine with others that have the same enthusiasm for vegetarian and vegan food that you do? Welcome to our group. Where the aim of Vegetarian Corner is to promote great friendships and harmonious connections. Stockholm has many excellent vegetarian and vegan restaurants, and new ones are opening all the time. Join us as we explore them all, and enjoy dining with some of the kindest, most gracious, most socially-conscious people in Stockholm Plus, join us as we go out on the town to vegetarian and vegan friendly bars and lounges. And partake when we go to visit some outstanding music venues. Great ways to have fun nights out on the town while in the company of a cool and compassionate group of vegetarians and vegans. We warmly welcome all vegetarians and vegans as well as those that are considering a vegetarian or vegan diet.
name: THE VEGETARIAN CORNER

category.name: food/drink
description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins
name: Vegan Hub Sthlm

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

description:
Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm! 

We'll be getting together for brunches and dinners that include everything from cheap eats to five star restaurants. We will also try to make social group deals/discount for our food and dinning group and we will announce them in a timely manner.

Please Note:
If we are eating at a restaurant where booking a table is needed, the organizer has to plan and book it.

Therefore we have two rules:
-Only RSVP if you are 100% sure you can come. If you change your RSVP from "Yes" to "No" two times within a short period for different meetups you cannot be a member of the group. So please only choose "yes" if you are sure you can come. 
-If you RSVP "Yes" and then don't come the meetup, same thing applies - you cannot be a member of the group.

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. Exploring and developing new recipes is fun, but in the end it is only me or my family eating my baked goods and we all know what too many cookies does to you! So I have an idea of a having a cookie recipe swap every now and then! People with a baking interest will meet, taste and give feedback on each others cookies and of course share the recipe with each other. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! Each meet up should have a theme, like chocolate, nuts, non bake, sponge cake, candy... well I think you know what Im getting at. Where we would meet depends completely on the number of people who would like to join in, perhaps we can find a suitable local as this meet up takes form.

description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters

description:
If you are looking for vegan food that is fully raw and awesome in taste and nutrition then you have found your place!

Welcome to Fully Rawsome group, a dedicated platform for creating rawfood events and workshops, providing you with full inspiration for a healthier lifestyle and a more nourishing diet.

Raw food is the healthiest food on planet, where minerals, vitamins and enzymes have not been destroyed by heat and where the life force of the food has been maintained.

Taking food in its raw form provides the body with maximum nutrition and enhances your own life force, hence feeling healthier, well nourished and energized.

Yet and to enjoy the intake of raw food, learning how to prepare delicious recipes makes your diet more fun and enjoyable and replace your unhealthy cravings with healthy ones.

Since there is much more than food for an awesome healthy life, this group will also include yoga and meditation events for a well nourished body, mind and soul.

Join us and stay tuned!

description:
I am passionate about cooking and used to organize such events in Austria. Now, as I am moving to Stockholm, I would like to do the same here. Usually it is somewhat of a casual fine dining event and the purpose of it all is to get to know new people and bring people together. It also gives me the opportunity to practice my cooking and improve. The dinner - usually 5 courses with drink accompaniment - will be offered at face value i.e. all I do is cover my costs, so I don’t earn anything. What I do get is new experience and knowledge. The menu and price will be published in advance and the number of people able to join will always be limited to 6. Hope to see you soon!


In the meantime you can follow me on instagram where I put up the food I cook. https://www.instagram.com/at_the_kitchen_ta...
name: At the kitchen table - Stockholm

category.name: food/drink
description:
Detta är en nystartad grupp för alla som brygger hemma i mindre skala i Göteborgsområdet och vill träffas för att byta erfarenheter och smaka varandras hembryggda öl för att på så sätt bli bättre på att brygga öl. 

Ditt bryggeri ska vara mellan 5-50 liter. Vilken typ av öl du brygger spelar ingen som helst roll. 

Själv har jag genomfört 6 st bryggningar och 110 liter totalt öl har blivit bryggt sedan December 2016. Jag brygger med BIAB-metoden och kan klämma ur 20-23 liter. 

Som en första träff tänker jag mig att man tar med ett par egenbryggda öl (om man har och vill) och träffas och smakar varandras öl och diskuterar hur vi brygger öl för att få tips och hjälp från varandra.
name: Göteborg home brew meetup

description:
All members who want to have a active fine wine and Micro Brew Beer Meetup group are welcome to join! We want to have wine or beer tasting events in members residence or perhaps in a wine bar or Micro Brew beer pub. We would also arrange events at a wine or beer merchant! No great knowledge of fine wine or micro brew beer is required to join this group just a love of micro brew fine beer and fine wine. This will be a fun social and active group! Active meaning if you post a idea it will not take long before it is posted as a Meetup! Speaking of active I would love to have assitant organizers who can also post Meetup events here! We will:

Organize tastings with merchants and in members homes or flats.


Trips to breweries or perhaps also to vineyards in France or Germany


So please join and please become a assitant organizer and help out!


Thanks to all!

description:
The Italian AVANTi​ Team presents 3 special evenings of Italy in a Sip where discovering and tasting 9 wines from a hidden gem in the heart of Italy.

A journey along exclusive wineries, surprising places, legends’ storytelling and gourmet appetisers.

We want to start this journey from a hidden gem of the Italian east coast located south of Venice: Le Marche Region. Just sticking with the genuine local tradition we would like you to travel with your taste and discover the beautiful hills, the charming valleys and the austere castles on top of the sea which surround these very special Italian vineyards and wineries. Inside each glass of wine we will find out Italy in a Sip!

description: Are you a woman approx. 25 - 40 years old and new in Copenhagen? Or are you just feeling like meeting some new people? Every now and then a group of max. 12 girls/women (to keep it at a proper size) meet in a café for a coffee and a chat. description:
This group is for anyone interested in veganism. The unifying theme for the meetup events is vegan food and lifestyle, but you don't have to be vegan to join this group and attend the events. However, the purpose of the group is for vegans to meet like-minded people and all meetup events are to be fully vegan.

A vegan avoids the consumption of animal products, hence a vegan diet is characterized by being a plant-based diet containing no animal products, i.e. no meat, no fish, no egg, no dairy products, and no honey.

There are several reasons for adopting a vegan lifestyle. In the video clip below Gary Yourofsky explains why you should become a vegan. He is very entertaining and it is really worth watching.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=es6U00LMmC4

You can also become vegan for a better health. See Michael Greger's annual talk about how you can avoid the most common diseases with a vegan diet:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d0IhZ-R1O8g
name: Copenhagen Vegan Meetup

category.name: food/drink
description:
My name is Kyle Dudley. I’m from Washington DC but lived in Copenhagen, Denmark for 7 years. Before I moved to Denmark I lived in Stockholm, Sweden or 5 years.

From 2010-13 I attended Copenhagen Hospitality College in Europe but after my second year of culinary school I was presented a opportunity to work at Out Of Denmark Restaurant in Delray Beach,Florida which was my introduction to fine dining. I have been cooking professionally for 6 years and worked the entire line (prep,grill,sauté etc)

For the last couple years my focal point has been combining Asian and Latin ingredients and developing a revolving menu to show case a variety of exotic fruits and vegetables. I called this concept Kuro Alma..”Kuro” meaning black in Japanese and “Alma” meaning soul in Spanish.

Enjoy and thank you, <br>

Chef Kyle
name: Kuro Alma Fusion | Asian-Latin Cuisine

category.name: food/drink
description:
All members who want to have a active fine wine and Micro Brew Beer Meetup group are welcome to join! We want to have wine or beer tasting events in members residence or perhaps in a wine bar or Micro Brew beer pub. We would also arrange events at a wine or beer merchant! No great knowledge of fine wine or micro brew beer is required to join this group just a love of micro brew fine beer and fine wine. This will be a fun social and active group! Active meaning if you post a idea it will not take long before it is posted as a Meetup! Speaking of active I would love to have assitant organizers who can also post Meetup events here! We will:

Organize tastings with merchants and in members homes or flats.


Trips to breweries or perhaps also to vineyards in France or Germany


So please join and please become a assitant organizer and help out!


Thanks to all!
name: Wine And Beer Lovers

category.name: food/drink
description:
The Italian AVANTi​ Team presents 3 special evenings of Italy in a Sip where discovering and tasting 9 wines from a hidden gem in the heart of Italy.

A journey along exclusive wineries, surprising places, legends’ storytelling and gourmet appetisers.

We want to start this journey from a hidden gem of the Italian east coast located south of Venice: Le Marche Region. Just sticking with the genuine local tradition we would like you to travel with your taste and discover the beautiful hills, the charming valleys and the austere castles on top of the sea which surround these very special Italian vineyards and wineries. Inside each glass of wine we will find out Italy in a Sip!
name: Italy in a Sip

category.name: food/drink
description:
Let's get together for specialty tea tasting once every two weeks. I'd love to meet like minded people passionate about whole leaf and unblended teas, to brew several different kinds of tea each time and discuss about taste, aroma, color, character of teas and tea culture in general. We talk how tea is picked, processed and made into the drink. We describe the different varieties, their characteristics and benefits, and how each should be brewed.I'd be happy to share my story as tea entrepreneur with you and learn more about the REAL tea together.

This tea tasting workshops is for group of eight people.
name: Tea Tasting Copenhagen

description:
This group is for anyone interested in veganism. The unifying theme for the meetup events is vegan food and lifestyle, but you don't have to be vegan to join this group and attend the events. However, the purpose of the group is for vegans to meet like-minded people and all meetup events are to be fully vegan.

A vegan avoids the consumption of animal products, hence a vegan diet is characterized by being a plant-based diet containing no animal products, i.e. no meat, no fish, no egg, no dairy products, and no honey.

There are several reasons for adopting a vegan lifestyle. In the video clip below Gary Yourofsky explains why you should become a vegan. He is very entertaining and it is really worth watching.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=es6U00LMmC4

You can also become vegan for a better health. See Michael Greger's annual talk about how you can avoid the most common diseases with a vegan diet:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d0IhZ-R1O8g
name: Copenhagen Vegan Meetup

category.name: food/drink
description:
My name is Kyle Dudley. I’m from Washington DC but lived in Copenhagen, Denmark for 7 years. Before I moved to Denmark I lived in Stockholm, Sweden or 5 years.

From 2010-13 I attended Copenhagen Hospitality College in Europe but after my second year of culinary school I was presented a opportunity to work at Out Of Denmark Restaurant in Delray Beach,Florida which was my introduction to fine dining. I have been cooking professionally for 6 years and worked the entire line (prep,grill,sauté etc)

For the last couple years my focal point has been combining Asian and Latin ingredients and developing a revolving menu to show case a variety of exotic fruits and vegetables. I called this concept Kuro Alma..”Kuro” meaning black in Japanese and “Alma” meaning soul in Spanish.

Enjoy and thank you, <br>

Chef Kyle
name: Kuro Alma Fusion | Asian-Latin Cuisine

category.name: food/drink
description:
Detta är en grupp som fokuserar på det sociala mötet i det offentliga rummet.
Det många anledningar till att ta en kaffe. Vissa dricker det för bli skarpare för stunden och för att kunna klara av de sista timmarna på jobbet. Andra dricker kaffet för sig själva i godan ro. Det finns till och med dem som dricker för mycket. Men det är något alldeles särskilt att en kaffe över ett fikabord. Att få samtala och möta en jämlik, öga mot öga!

Just den här gruppen fokuserar inte på kaffet lika mycket som den fokuserar på det sociala mötet. (Vad man väljer att dricka är upp till var och en.)
Motivationen för den här gruppen är att det spontana mötet inte händer lika mycket idag som det gjorde igår i det alltmer digitaliserade samhället.

• Behöver du snacka av dig efter jobbet eller skolan?
• Har du en stund till övers?
• Suktar du efter det goda samtalet?

Låt oss då dela med av oss över en kopp kaffe!
name: Karlstad | Kaffesnacket

category.name: food/drink
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in cooking, eating out, meeting new people, discovering new cultures and make new friends.
Once a week we will meet up at someones home, and one of us will choose a dish to cook and eat together. We will try to choose a dish from different cultures each week (Japanese/French/itailan/spanish etc.) and one time every forth week or so we will go out and eat at a restaurant together.
You don't have to be a good chef to take part, you just have to think it is fun.
I would love to see as many people from different cultures as possible so we can get a big variation of food experience! And we can also have some language exchange.
Does this sound fun? Then sign up!
name: Jönköping Cooking and language exchange Meetup

Are you a chile-head? Do you eat chile-peppers, hot sauces, spicy dishes, etc.? Are you interested in growing your own chile pepper plants? If you answered yes to some of the questions, please join Göteborg Chile Peppers Meetup - GOT Hot & Spicy Foodies.

This Meetup groups is about hot & spicy food stuff, including hot sauces, spices, dishes (e.g., Thai and Indian), different types of chile peppers (chillies, paprika).

The ideal member is a hot & spicy foodie. The members are called chile-heads (as in chile pepper lovers).

You should join if you want to learn more about chile peppers in different ways. 

We will share recipes, chile pepper seeds / plants, discussing Scoville units, meeting at restaurants serving hot & spicy food, etc.

category.name: food/drink
description:
Detta är en nystartad grupp för alla som brygger hemma i mindre skala i Göteborgsområdet och vill träffas för att byta erfarenheter och smaka varandras hembryggda öl för att på så sätt bli bättre på att brygga öl. 

Ditt bryggeri ska vara mellan 5-50 liter. Vilken typ av öl du brygger spelar ingen som helst roll. 

Själv har jag genomfört 6 st bryggningar och 110 liter totalt öl har blivit bryggt sedan December 2016. Jag brygger med BIAB-metoden och kan klämma ur 20-23 liter. 

Som en första träff tänker jag mig att man tar med ett par egenbryggda öl (om man har och vill) och träffas och smakar varandras öl och diskuterar hur vi brygger öl för att få tips och hjälp från varandra.

description: Do you love trying new vegetarian & vegan restaurants? Do you enjoy the company of fellow vegetarians & vegans? Do you wish to dine with others that have the same enthusiasm for vegetarian and vegan food that you do? Welcome to our group. Where the aim of Vegetarian Corner is to promote great friendships and harmonious connections. Stockholm has many excellent vegetarian and vegan restaurants, and new ones are opening all the time. Join us as we explore them all, and enjoy dining with some of the kindest, most gracious, most socially-conscious people in Stockholm Plus, join us as we go out on the town to vegetarian and vegan friendly bars and lounges. And partake when we go to visit some outstanding music venues. Great ways to have fun nights out on the town while in the company of a cool and compassionate group of vegetarians and vegans. We warmly welcome all vegetarians and vegans as well as those that are considering a vegetarian or vegan diet.

category.name: food/drink
description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins
name: Vegan Hub Sthlm

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

description:
Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm! 

We'll be getting together for brunches and dinners that include everything from cheap eats to five star restaurants. We will also try to make social group deals/discount for our food and dinning group and we will announce them in a timely manner.

Please Note:
If we are eating at a restaurant where booking a table is needed, the organizer has to plan and book it.

Therefore we have two rules:
-Only RSVP if you are 100% sure you can come. If you change your RSVP from "Yes" to "No" two times within a short period for different meetups you cannot be a member of the group. So please only choose "yes" if you are sure you can come. 
-If you RSVP "Yes" and then don't come the meetup, same thing applies - you cannot be a member of the group.

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. Exploring and developing new recipes is fun, but in the end it is only me or my family eating my baked goods and we all know what too many cookies does to you! So I have an idea of a having a cookie recipe swap every now and then! People with a baking interest will meet, taste and give feedback on each others cookies and of course share the recipe with each other. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! Each meet up should have a theme, like chocolate, nuts, non bake, sponge cake, candy... well I think you know what Im getting at. Where we would meet depends completely on the number of people who would like to join in, perhaps we can find a suitable local as this meet up takes form.

description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

description:
One city, three courses – and hundreds of memories <br> Enjoy the winter season with new friends and a full stomach. At Running Dinner, you share your special dish (or learn one) and get insights into other people’s cooking styles. You enjoy homemade cuisine at the homes of fellow food lovers in Stockholm. If you are fed up with making tacos and hearing the same old buzz stories, we invite you to this culinary adventure that will serve both body and mind. Together with the three-course menu, you will explore new neighbourhoods and enjoy fascinating conversations. Sign up for this culinary journey in Stockholm on 28th of January!

Still hesitating? Check out this article from Svenska Dagbladet's food critic: http://bit.ly/1AvKPCT <br>

category.name: food/drink
description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters
organizer.name: Dan Fukushima

description:
If you are looking for vegan food that is fully raw and awesome in taste and nutrition then you have found your place!

Welcome to Fully Rawsome group, a dedicated platform for creating rawfood events and workshops, providing you with full inspiration for a healthier lifestyle and a more nourishing diet.

Raw food is the healthiest food on planet, where minerals, vitamins and enzymes have not been destroyed by heat and where the life force of the food has been maintained.

Taking food in its raw form provides the body with maximum nutrition and enhances your own life force, hence feeling healthier, well nourished and energized.

Yet and to enjoy the intake of raw food, learning how to prepare delicious recipes makes your diet more fun and enjoyable and replace your unhealthy cravings with healthy ones.

Since there is much more than food for an awesome healthy life, this group will also include yoga and meditation events for a well nourished body, mind and soul.

Join us and stay tuned!

description:
I am passionate about cooking and used to organize such events in Austria. Now, as I am moving to Stockholm, I would like to do the same here. Usually it is somewhat of a casual fine dining event and the purpose of it all is to get to know new people and bring people together. It also gives me the opportunity to practice my cooking and improve. The dinner - usually 5 courses with drink accompaniment - will be offered at face value i.e. all I do is cover my costs, so I don’t earn anything. What I do get is new experience and knowledge. The menu and price will be published in advance and the number of people able to join will always be limited to 6. Hope to see you soon!


In the meantime you can follow me on instagram where I put up the food I cook. https://www.instagram.com/at_the_kitchen_ta...

description:
Detta är en nystartad grupp för alla som brygger hemma i mindre skala i Göteborgsområdet och vill träffas för att byta erfarenheter och smaka varandras hembryggda öl för att på så sätt bli bättre på att brygga öl. 

Ditt bryggeri ska vara mellan 5-50 liter. Vilken typ av öl du brygger spelar ingen som helst roll. 

Själv har jag genomfört 6 st bryggningar och 110 liter totalt öl har blivit bryggt sedan December 2016. Jag brygger med BIAB-metoden och kan klämma ur 20-23 liter. 

Som en första träff tänker jag mig att man tar med ett par egenbryggda öl (om man har och vill) och träffas och smakar varandras öl och diskuterar hur vi brygger öl för att få tips och hjälp från varandra.

description: Do you love trying new vegetarian & vegan restaurants? Do you enjoy the company of fellow vegetarians & vegans? description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm!

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

category.name: food/drink
description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters

description:
If you are looking for vegan food that is fully raw and awesome in taste and nutrition then you have found your place!

Welcome to Fully Rawsome group, a dedicated platform for creating rawfood events and workshops, providing you with full inspiration for a healthier lifestyle and a more nourishing diet.

Raw food is the healthiest food on planet, where minerals, vitamins and enzymes have not been destroyed by heat and where the life force of the food has been maintained.

Taking food in its raw form provides the body with maximum nutrition and enhances your own life force, hence feeling healthier, well nourished and energized.

Yet and to enjoy the intake of raw food, learning how to prepare delicious recipes makes your diet more fun and enjoyable and replace your unhealthy cravings with healthy ones.

Since there is much more than food for an awesome healthy life, this group will also include yoga and meditation events for a well nourished body, mind and soul.

Join us and stay tuned!
name: Fully Rawsome!  Raw & Vegan - Yoga & Meditation

description:
I am passionate about cooking and used to organize such events in Austria. Now, as I am moving to Stockholm, I would like to do the same here. Usually it is somewhat of a casual fine dining event and the purpose of it all is to get to know new people and bring people together. It also gives me the opportunity to practice my cooking and improve. The dinner - usually 5 courses with drink accompaniment - will be offered at face value i.e. all I do is cover my costs, so I don’t earn anything. What I do get is new experience and knowledge. The menu and price will be published in advance and the number of people able to join will always be limited to 6. Hope to see you soon!


In the meantime you can follow me on instagram where I put up the food I cook. https://www.instagram.com/at_the_kitchen_ta...

category.name: food/drink
description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins
name: Vegan Hub Sthlm

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

description:
Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm! 

We'll be getting together for brunches and dinners that include everything from cheap eats to five star restaurants. We will also try to make social group deals/discount for our food and dinning group and we will announce them in a timely manner.

Please Note:
If we are eating at a restaurant where booking a table is needed, the organizer has to plan and book it.

Therefore we have two rules:
-Only RSVP if you are 100% sure you can come. If you change your RSVP from "Yes" to "No" two times within a short period for different meetups you cannot be a member of the group. So please only choose "yes" if you are sure you can come. 
-If you RSVP "Yes" and then don't come the meetup, same thing applies - you cannot be a member of the group.

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. Exploring and developing new recipes is fun, but in the end it is only me or my family eating my baked goods and we all know what too many cookies does to you! So I have an idea of a having a cookie recipe swap every now and then! People with a baking interest will meet, taste and give feedback on each others cookies and of course share the recipe with each other. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! Each meet up should have a theme, like chocolate, nuts, non bake, sponge cake, candy... well I think you know what Im getting at. Where we would meet depends completely on the number of people who would like to join in, perhaps we can find a suitable local as this meet up takes form.

category.name: food/drink
description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

category.name: food/drink
description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters

description:
If you are looking for vegan food that is fully raw and awesome in taste and nutrition then you have found your place!

Welcome to Fully Rawsome group, a dedicated platform for creating rawfood events and workshops, providing you with full inspiration for a healthier lifestyle and a more nourishing diet.

Raw food is the healthiest food on planet, where minerals, vitamins and enzymes have not been destroyed by heat and where the life force of the food has been maintained.

Taking food in its raw form provides the body with maximum nutrition and enhances your own life force, hence feeling healthier, well nourished and energized.

Yet and to enjoy the intake of raw food, learning how to prepare delicious recipes makes your diet more fun and enjoyable and replace your unhealthy cravings with healthy ones.

Since there is much more than food for an awesome healthy life, this group will also include yoga and meditation events for a well nourished body, mind and soul.

Join us and stay tuned!

description:
I am passionate about cooking and used to organize such events in Austria. Now, as I am moving to Stockholm, I would like to do the same here. Usually it is somewhat of a casual fine dining event and the purpose of it all is to get to know new people and bring people together. It also gives me the opportunity to practice my cooking and improve. The dinner - usually 5 courses with drink accompaniment - will be offered at face value i.e. all I do is cover my costs, so I don’t earn anything. What I do get is new experience and knowledge. The menu and price will be published in advance and the number of people able to join will always be limited to 6. Hope to see you soon!


In the meantime you can follow me on instagram where I put up the food I cook. https://www.instagram.com/at_the_kitchen_ta...

description: Do you love trying new vegetarian & vegan restaurants? Do you enjoy the company of fellow vegetarians & vegans? Do you wish to dine with others that have the same enthusiasm for vegetarian and vegan food that you do? Welcome to our group. Where the aim of Vegetarian Corner is to promote great friendships and harmonious connections. Stockholm has many excellent vegetarian and vegan restaurants, and new ones are opening all the time. Join us as we explore them all, and enjoy dining with some of the kindest, most gracious, most socially-conscious people in Stockholm Plus, join us as we go out on the town to vegetarian and vegan friendly bars and lounges. And partake when we go to visit some outstanding music venues. Great ways to have fun nights out on the town while in the company of a cool and compassionate group of vegetarians and vegans. We warmly welcome all vegetarians and vegans as well as those that are considering a vegetarian or vegan diet.

category.name: food/drink
description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins
name: Vegan Hub Sthlm
organizer.name: Axo Sal (Azamat Salakhov)

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

description:
Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm! 

We'll be getting together for brunches and dinners that include everything from cheap eats to five star restaurants. We will also try to make social group deals/discount for our food and dinning group and we will announce them in a timely manner.

Please Note:
If we are eating at a restaurant where booking a table is needed, the organizer has to plan and book it.

Therefore we have two rules:
-Only RSVP if you are 100% sure you can come. If you change your RSVP from "Yes" to "No" two times within a short period for different meetups you cannot be a member of the group. So please only choose "yes" if you are sure you can come. 
-If you RSVP "Yes" and then don't come the meetup, same thing applies - you cannot be a member of the group.

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. Exploring and developing new recipes is fun, but in the end it is only me or my family eating my baked goods and we all know what too many cookies does to you! So I have an idea of a having a cookie recipe swap every now and then! People with a baking interest will meet, taste and give feedback on each others cookies and of course share the recipe with each other. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! Each meet up should have a theme, like chocolate, nuts, non bake, sponge cake, candy... well I think you know what Im getting at. Where we would meet depends completely on the number of people who would like to join in, perhaps we can find a suitable local as this meet up takes form.

description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

description:
One city, three courses – and hundreds of memories <br> Enjoy the winter season with new friends and a full stomach. At Running Dinner, you share your special dish (or learn one) and get insights into other people’s cooking styles. You enjoy homemade cuisine at the homes of fellow food lovers in Stockholm. If you are fed up with making tacos and hearing the same old buzz stories, we invite you to this culinary adventure that will serve both body and mind. Together with the three-course menu, you will explore new neighbourhoods and enjoy fascinating conversations. Sign up for this culinary journey in Stockholm on 28th of January!

Still hesitating? Check out this article from Svenska Dagbladet's food critic: http://bit.ly/1AvKPCT <br>

description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters

description:
If you are looking for vegan food that is fully raw and awesome in taste and nutrition then you have found your place!

Welcome to Fully Rawsome group, a dedicated platform for creating rawfood events and workshops, providing you with full inspiration for a healthier lifestyle and a more nourishing diet.

Raw food is the healthiest food on planet, where minerals, vitamins and enzymes have not been destroyed by heat and where the life force of the food has been maintained.

Taking food in its raw form provides the body with maximum nutrition and enhances your own life force, hence feeling healthier, well nourished and energized.

Yet and to enjoy the intake of raw food, learning how to prepare delicious recipes makes your diet more fun and enjoyable and replace your unhealthy cravings with healthy ones.

Since there is much more than food for an awesome healthy life, this group will also include yoga and meditation events for a well nourished body, mind and soul.

Join us and stay tuned!

category.name: food/drink
description:
I am passionate about cooking and used to organize such events in Austria. Now, as I am moving to Stockholm, I would like to do the same here. Usually it is somewhat of a casual fine dining event and the purpose of it all is to get to know new people and bring people together. It also gives me the opportunity to practice my cooking and improve. The dinner - usually 5 courses with drink accompaniment - will be offered at face value i.e. all I do is cover my costs, so I don’t earn anything. What I do get is new experience and knowledge. The menu and price will be published in advance and the number of people able to join will always be limited to 6. Hope to see you soon!


In the meantime you can follow me on instagram where I put up the food I cook. https://www.instagram.com/at_the_kitchen_ta...
name: At the kitchen table - Stockholm

description:
All members who want to have a active fine wine and Micro Brew Beer Meetup group are welcome to join! We want to have wine or beer tasting events in members residence or perhaps in a wine bar or Micro Brew beer pub. We would also arrange events at a wine or beer merchant! No great knowledge of fine wine or micro brew beer is required to join this group just a love of micro brew fine beer and fine wine. This will be a fun social and active group! Active meaning if you post a idea it will not take long before it is posted as a Meetup! Speaking of active I would love to have assitant organizers who can also post Meetup events here! We will:

Organize tastings with merchants and in members homes or flats.


Trips to breweries or perhaps also to vineyards in France or Germany


So please join and please become a assitant organizer and help out!


Thanks to all!

category.name: food/drink
description:
The Italian AVANTi​ Team presents 3 special evenings of Italy in a Sip where discovering and tasting 9 wines from a hidden gem in the heart of Italy.

A journey along exclusive wineries, surprising places, legends’ storytelling and gourmet appetisers.

We want to start this journey from a hidden gem of the Italian east coast located south of Venice: Le Marche Region. Just sticking with the genuine local tradition we would like you to travel with your taste and discover the beautiful hills, the charming valleys and the austere castles on top of the sea which surround these very special Italian vineyards and wineries. Inside each glass of wine we will find out Italy in a Sip!
name: Italy in a Sip

description:
Let's get together for specialty tea tasting once every two weeks. I'd love to meet like minded people passionate about whole leaf and unblended teas, to brew several different kinds of tea each time and discuss about taste, aroma, color, character of teas and tea culture in general. We talk how tea is picked, processed and made into the drink. We describe the different varieties, their characteristics and benefits, and how each should be brewed.I'd be happy to share my story as tea entrepreneur with you and learn more about the REAL tea together.

This tea tasting workshops is for group of eight people.

description:
This group is for anyone interested in veganism. The unifying theme for the meetup events is vegan food and lifestyle, but you don't have to be vegan to join this group and attend the events. However, the purpose of the group is for vegans to meet like-minded people and all meetup events are to be fully vegan.

A vegan avoids the consumption of animal products, hence a vegan diet is characterized by being a plant-based diet containing no animal products, i.e. no meat, no fish, no egg, no dairy products, and no honey.

There are several reasons for adopting a vegan lifestyle. In the video clip below Gary Yourofsky explains why you should become a vegan. He is very entertaining and it is really worth watching.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=es6U00LMmC4

You can also become vegan for a better health. See Michael Greger's annual talk about how you can avoid the most common diseases with a vegan diet:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d0IhZ-R1O8g
name: Copenhagen Vegan Meetup

category.name: food/drink
description:
My name is Kyle Dudley. I’m from Washington DC but lived in Copenhagen, Denmark for 7 years. Before I moved to Denmark I lived in Stockholm, Sweden or 5 years.

From 2010-13 I attended Copenhagen Hospitality College in Europe but after my second year of culinary school I was presented a opportunity to work at Out Of Denmark Restaurant in Delray Beach,Florida which was my introduction to fine dining. I have been cooking professionally for 6 years and worked the entire line (prep,grill,sauté etc)

For the last couple years my focal point has been combining Asian and Latin ingredients and developing a revolving menu to show case a variety of exotic fruits and vegetables. I called this concept Kuro Alma..”Kuro” meaning black in Japanese and “Alma” meaning soul in Spanish.

Enjoy and thank you, <br>

Chef Kyle
name: Kuro Alma Fusion | Asian-Latin Cuisine

Are you a chile-head? Do you eat chile-peppers, hot sauces, spicy dishes, etc.? Are you interested in growing your own chile pepper plants? If you answered yes to some of the questions, please join Göteborg Chile Peppers Meetup - GOT Hot & Spicy Foodies.

This Meetup groups is about hot & spicy food stuff, including hot sauces, spices, dishes (e.g., Thai and Indian), different types of chile peppers (chillies, paprika).

The ideal member is a hot & spicy foodie. The members are called chile-heads (as in chile pepper lovers).

You should join if you want to learn more about chile peppers in different ways. 

We will share recipes, chile pepper seeds / plants, discussing Scoville units, meeting at restaurants serving hot & spicy food, etc.

category.name: food/drink
description:
Detta är en nystartad grupp för alla som brygger hemma i mindre skala i Göteborgsområdet och vill träffas för att byta erfarenheter och smaka varandras hembryggda öl för att på så sätt bli bättre på att brygga öl. 

Ditt bryggeri ska vara mellan 5-50 liter. Vilken typ av öl du brygger spelar ingen som helst roll. 

Själv har jag genomfört 6 st bryggningar och 110 liter totalt öl har blivit bryggt sedan December 2016. Jag brygger med BIAB-metoden och kan klämma ur 20-23 liter. 

Som en första träff tänker jag mig att man tar med ett par egenbryggda öl (om man har och vill) och träffas och smakar varandras öl och diskuterar hur vi brygger öl för att få tips och hjälp från varandra.
name: Göteborg home brew meetup
organizer.name: Niklas Johansson

description: Do you love trying new vegetarian & vegan restaurants? Do you enjoy the company of fellow vegetarians & vegans? Where the aim of Vegetarian Corner is to promote great friendships and harmonious connections. Stockholm has many excellent vegetarian and vegan restaurants, and new ones are opening all the time. Join us as we explore them all, and enjoy dining with some of the kindest, most gracious, most socially-conscious people in Stockholm Plus, join us as we go out on the town to vegetarian and vegan friendly bars and lounges. And partake when we go to visit some outstanding music venues. Great ways to have fun nights out on the town while in the company of a cool and compassionate group of vegetarians and vegans. We warmly welcome all vegetarians and vegans as well as those that are considering a vegetarian or vegan diet.
name: THE VEGETARIAN CORNER

description:
Seasoned, new and aspiring vegans are invited to get together and share ideas, tips, insights, experiences, recipes, knowledge, skills...the list goes on! Lets make life easier for ourselves, show others how simple it can be and encourage the spread of veganism in a non-militant way. We are all humans here: sometimes it is not always possible to be strictly vegan, sometimes people don't understand and sometimes life just gets in the way of our best efforts. And then sometimes it's just nice to be around like-minded people who appreciate the conscious choices we make as part of our lifestyle.


OUR NEW NO-SHOW POLICY

Dear vegans,

Since some meetups require proper planning and booking of specific venues in advance, we have decided to create these new rules, to help us in organizing the meetups better.

We encourage everyone to be mindful of others and update your RSVPs as early as possible, since we have a waiting list most of the time.

- 3 (three) No-Shows or Late Cancellations will result in your removal from the group.

- each member that RSVP and did not show-up will receive an email or message reminding them about our new policy and that they have a warning.

- Cancellations less than 12 hours before an event start time are considered "Late Cancellations" and may count as a No Show.

**Your Event Host may lengthen or shorten this time frame depending on the venue, etc. but we all strive to be as fair and flexible as possible.

Thanking you in advance,

The Vegan Hub Sthlm Admins
name: Vegan Hub Sthlm

description:
Our purpose is to give you inspiration and tools to make your everyday cooking easier and more creative. 

It doesn't matter on which level you are in your cooking knowledge or which budget you have. This group is for everyone that wants to shape up their daily cooking, eat less take away/ready to eat dishes and learn how to transform the food available at home. <br>

By lectures, workshops and by inviting people with different expertise in the food area we will get you inspired in your cooking. To bring enthusiasm and inspiration to everyone attending we need the meet ups to be dynamic. Therefore we encourage our members to be active in discussions and share their own tips with the rest of the group. Or why not host your own meetup here!?

Behind the group is Kalle Söderman. Kalle offers an online service with IngredientMatcher, that shows you new recipes you can make with the ingredients you already have at home!

Welcome to Cooking in Stockholm! – For easier better cooking

description:
Do you love dining out? Do you like to explore new cuisines, restaurants and good foods? Does the idea of making new friends and having great conversations appeal to you? If you've answered yes to any of the above, then join us as we eat our way through Stockholm! 

We'll be getting together for brunches and dinners that include everything from cheap eats to five star restaurants. We will also try to make social group deals/discount for our food and dinning group and we will announce them in a timely manner.

Please Note:
If we are eating at a restaurant where booking a table is needed, the organizer has to plan and book it.

description: Do you like to bake? Me too! Unfortunately I rarely have an occasion to make the extra effort with my baking, other than perhaps for birthdays and holidays. Exploring and developing new recipes is fun, but in the end it is only me or my family eating my baked goods and we all know what too many cookies does to you! So I have an idea of a having a cookie recipe swap every now and then! People with a baking interest will meet, taste and give feedback on each others cookies and of course share the recipe with each other. You can use your favourite classic recipe, the old family recipe, search the internet for a new or if you feel creative, make a new recipe! Each meet up should have a theme, like chocolate, nuts, non bake, sponge cake, candy... well I think you know what Im getting at. description: Are you new in town and looking to get to know some people in the city who you can try that great new restaurant with or simply a glass of wine after work? This is a group for people who enjoy going to restaurants and bars, but would prefer the event wasn't completely centered around the food and drinks themselves. It's a group for anyone and everyone who is passionate about something and ready to put themselves out there to meet new people and try new places. Event sizes will be kept intimate but frequent, as the main purpose here is that we can get to know each other and form genuine friendships with those who are part of the group (while of course trying out a whole lot of great food, wine and beer along the way!) Some similar groups tend to have a lot of people attending the events, which can make it a little difficult to get to know each other, and can be a little overwhelming for some. I will be trying to keep dinner groups to 8, but will extend to 10 for events with a high interest. I will post events frequently though so everyone can have a chance to join! If the group grows, we can re-evaluate. I highly encourage any members to add their own events to this group as well. Heard of a great bar and want to check it out on a Friday? Post an event! Happy dining / drinking / chatting! Looking forward to meeting you all.

category.name: food/drink
description: This is a group for all people interested in wine and wine tasting. We will arrange tastings for small groups where each of us will bring a bottle, give a short presentation and taste it. We will meet in the apartment of one of the two organizers who will kindly share his kitchen and glasses for the love of wine. We will have a theme for each occasion to give the selection a context. Everyone is welcome to join in regardless of your level of knowledge or age. The purpose is to create a fun and inclusive social space for people to meet and learn about wine. My co-organizer and I came up with the idea to create this group after recently having moved back to Sweden. Where I previously lived I used to gather with wine loving friends where each of us would bring a bottle and cook something, or meet up in a BYOB restaurant. This was a great way to get to taste many different wines and more importantly, to enjoy wine the way it is meant to - in the company of other people. If you are all alone it will cost you a lot to cork up six bottles and perhaps even make you feel miserable, but if we do it together, we will have a nice time and probably also lots of fun. About myself: I am half Japanese half Swedish and have spent almost half of my life in both countries. I was recently working with French wine for an importer in Tokyo where I had the opportunity to experience many mind-blowing wines, as well as amazing people who have devoted their lives to the spread of high quality drinks. I am educated in two different wine schools where I have studied for JSA Wine expert, WSET level three, SSI Sake Sommelier, and I am currently enrolled in an online course for the WSET Diploma. I enjoy all sorts of wine, but I tend to be most interested in wines with personality, representing either history, typicity or the personality of the wine maker. In tastings however, I like to encounter everything from large-scale productions to the work of small boutique wineries of all corners of the world. There’s a jungle of wine out there so let’s get together and explore it!
name: Stockholm Wine Tasters
